<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>üöÄ LibCarla APT Repository</h1>
            <p>Official CARLA Client Library Packages</p>
        </header>
        
        <main>
            <div class="section">
                <h2>üì¶ Installation</h2>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3><span class="step-number">1</span>Add the repository GPG key</h3>
                    <div class="code-block">curl -fsSL https://${REPO_OWNER}.github.io/${REPO_NAME}/public.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/libcarla-archive-keyring.gpg</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3><span class="step-number">2</span>Add the repository</h3>
                    <div class="code-block">echo "deb [arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/libcarla-archive-keyring.gpg] https://${REPO_OWNER}.github.io/${REPO_NAME} stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/libcarla.list</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <h3><span class="step-number">3</span>Update and install</h3>
                    <div class="code-block">sudo apt-get update<br>sudo apt-get install libcarla</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>üìã Available Packages</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>libcarla</strong> - CARLA client library with headers and development files</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>üñ•Ô∏è Supported Distributions</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ubuntu 22.04 (amd64, arm64)</li>
                    <li>Ubuntu 24.04 (amd64, arm64)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>‚ÑπÔ∏è Repository Information</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Origin:</strong> the78mole/libcarla</li>
                    <li><strong>Components:</strong> main</li>
                    <li><strong>Architectures:</strong> amd64, arm64</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>üí° Manual Download:</strong> You can also download .deb packages directly from the 
                <a href="https://github.com/${REPO_OWNER}/${REPO_NAME}/releases" target="_blank">GitHub Releases</a> page.
            </div>
            
            <div class="warning-box">
                <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Note:</strong> This repository is for development purposes. Make sure you have the appropriate 
                CARLA server version compatible with the client library.
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>üîç Testing the Repository</h2>
                <p>To verify the repository is working correctly:</p>
                <div class="code-block">
<span class="comment"># Check if the repository is accessible</span>
curl -I https://${REPO_OWNER}.github.io/${REPO_NAME}/dists/stable/Release

<span class="comment"># List available packages</span>
apt-cache policy libcarla

<span class="comment"># View package information</span>
apt show libcarla
                </div>
            </div>
